## Session Tree Structure

### File Format (JSONL)

```jsonl
{"type":"session","version":3,"id":"uuid","timestamp":"...","cwd":"/path"}
{"type":"message","id":"a1b2c3d4","parentId":null,"timestamp":"...","message":{...}}
{"type":"message","id":"b2c3d4e5","parentId":"a1b2c3d4","timestamp":"...","message":{...}}
{"type":"model_change","id":"c3d4e5f6","parentId":"b2c3d4e5","timestamp":"...","provider":"openai","modelId":"gpt-4o"}
{"type":"message","id":"d4e5f6g7","parentId":"a1b2c3d4","timestamp":"...","message":{...}}  ← branch
```

### Entry Types

```typescript
type SessionEntry =
  | SessionMessageEntry      // AgentMessage wrapped with id/parentId
  | ModelChangeEntry         // provider, modelId
  | ThinkingLevelChangeEntry // thinkingLevel
  | CompactionEntry          // summary, firstKeptEntryId, tokensBefore
  | BranchSummaryEntry       // fromId, summary
  | CustomEntry              // customType, data (extension state, NOT in LLM context)
  | CustomMessageEntry       // customType, content, display (IN LLM context)
  | LabelEntry               // targetId, label (user bookmarks)
  | SessionInfoEntry         // name (display name)
```

### Context Building

```typescript
// SessionManager.buildSessionContext() walks from leaf to root:
// 1. Collect all entries on path
// 2. Extract current model/thinking level (latest wins)
// 3. If compaction on path:
//    - Emit compactionSummary message first
//    - Emit messages from firstKeptEntryId to compaction
//    - Emit messages after compaction
// 4. Convert branchSummary/customMessage to appropriate formats

interface SessionContext {
  messages: AgentMessage[];
  thinkingLevel: string;
  model: { provider: string; modelId: string } | null;
}
```

